comment_regular_data.body:
It seems like `nlua_exec` sets the `'<nvim>'` string for the context. Would it be okay here to add a 'optional' param `chunkname` that can set the chunkname? Currently nlua_exec seems to be called 5 times in total, so the additional LOC changes are low. I.e.:

From:
```c
/// @param[in]  str  String to execute.
/// @param[in]  args array of ... args
/// @param[in]  mode Whether and how the the return value should be converted to Object
/// @param[in] arena  can be NULL, then nested allocations are used
/// @param[out]  err  Location where error will be saved.
```

To:
```c
/// @param[in]  str  String to execute.
/// @param[in]  chunkname Optional chunkname for executed Lua string.
/// @param[in]  args array of ... args
/// @param[in]  mode Whether and how the the return value should be converted to Object
/// @param[in] arena  can be NULL, then nested allocations are used
/// @param[out]  err  Location where error will be saved.
```
